  <heading>EXPAND</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Copy lower-numbered vector elements to Active elements</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction copies consecutive elements
from the source vector to Active elements of the destination vector,
in increasing order of element number.
Inactive elements in the destination vector register are set to zero.</para>
      <para>This instruction is illegal when executed in
Streaming SVE mode, unless FEAT_SME_FA64 is implemented and enabled,
or FEAT_SME2p2 is implemented.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
    <sm_policy>SM_0_or_SME2p2</sm_policy>
  </desc>
